description:
Renfrewshire Council is planning to issue a tender for a contract for Works to Roads Related Structures. The contract may consist of the following types of works:
 -Bridge Strengthening/ Replacement;
 -Scour Protection Works;
 -Parapet Upgrading;
 -Bridge Joint Replacement;
 -General Bridge Maintenance;
 -Retaining Wall Strengthening/ Replacement;
 -Traffic management requirements;
 -any associated or ancillary works; and
 -any of the work the Contractor is to design
 In providing the works, the Contractor shall:
 -Design, supply, install, maintain and remove all traffic management measures and associated diversions.
 This list is indicative only and is subject to change. The Invitation to Tender will provide detail of the Council's requirement when it is published. Contractors who are interested in this opportunity are invited to completed and return the questionnaire attached to this Prior Information Notice should they wish to do so.

The SPS provides a fully managed vending service across its entire estate. This service offers staff and visitors convenient access to a range of refreshments, including hot drinks, cold drinks, snacks, and confectionery. In addition, sites can opt to include freshâfood vending machines where required. All vending provision is aligned with the NHS Healthy Living Award criteria, ensuring healthier choices are available and promoted.
 The appointed supplier is responsible for the full operation of each machine. This includes:
 -Regular stocking and replenishment of products;
 -Routine cleaning and hygiene maintenance;
 -Technical upkeep, repairs, and general maintenance; and
 -Service visits at a frequency agreed with each individual site.
